+commentary/spoilers

-this


Okay, this is going to be a weird one to explain  so bear with me while I try to deconstruct this for y'all.

Basically, what I wanted to achieve with the article was this: I wanted it to be layered. There are multiple possible ways of interpreting what's going on here, but the real symbolic 'meat' of the article comes (for me at least) when you start pulling it apart. I took an SCP about writing a fictional SCP, and intentionally made it slightly unclear whether it was actually fictional  after all, as scary as the SCP (wiki) might be, there's no way it could possibly be real.

Everything from the title to the core idea is designed to mimic and parody the reading and writing of SCP articles, both in-universe and out, and I honestly don't care whether it came through at all  it's the most 'artsy' thing I've ever attempted, and I'm proud of the result.

To conclude, I want to stress that there isn't any canonical answer to which interpretation is correct: there are three layers of meta going on here, and picking them apart to find an answer is downright impossible. There simply isn't enough information there. I have a headcanon for which is the 'real' one, if that term can be applied to a fictional narrative about a (maybe) fictional document about a (maybe) fictional creature, but that doesn't make yours any less correct. After all, it's just a story.








